Operating as a grassroots entity, the organization focuses on refugee advocacy and direct aid for one of the world's most persecuted communities. In the 2023 fiscal year, the charity managed a <cite id="2">total revenue of $79,249</cite>, reflecting its status as a small-scale, focused provider in the humanitarian sector. Despite its modest size, the organization demonstrates a remarkable commitment to financial efficiency, reporting a <cite id="1">100.0% program expense ratio</cite>, which indicates that all functional expenses are directed toward its core mission. Furthermore, the charity maintains <cite id="1">high fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending $0.00 to raise every $1 of income. This lean operational model ensures that donor contributions are maximized for direct service delivery, although the organization's <cite id="2">total assets of $23,205</cite> suggest a limited financial cushion for rapid expansion. The charity currently holds an <cite id="1">overall score of 67.67.5/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, which reflects a combination of strong financial health and areas for growth in leadership and transparency documentation.
